news.title: UK annual house prices slow for third month in a row: Halifax
news.para: Prices rose by 10.5% compared with May last year, down from April's 10.8% increase to show the smallest increase since January.

news.title: Special PMLA court directs CBI to restore DHFL promoter's custody to Taloja prison
news.para: Wadhwan’s lawyers had approached the court contending that the transfer to UP was “ prima facie not as per law” as they were taken from Taloja jail without the court’s permission or knowledge.

news.title: Turkey set to cap rent increases at 25% as inflation soars
news.para: Annual inflation hit its highest since 1998 at 73.5% last month due to soaring energy prices and an easing cycle by the central bank in accordance with President Tayyip Erdogan's economic plan that prioritises production, exports, growth and low rates.

news.title: Ludhiana: Draw of lots for Atal apartments on June 16
news.para: Land acquisition collector (LAC) Neetu Katyal on Thursday reviewed the final arrangements for this mega event scheduled to be held on June 16 at Nehru Siddhant Kendra.

news.title: Polycab India promoter buys duplex in Mumbai's Prabhadevi for Rs 48 crore
news.para: In November, Hindalco Industries, part of the Aditya Birla Group, had acquired a 100% equity stake in Polycab India’s wholly-owned subsidiary Ryker Base Private Ltd for an enterprise value of Rs 323 crore.

news.title: Dalmia Bharat committed to invest Rs 9,000-crore to expand its manufacturing capacity
news.para: Dalmia Bharat has a Cement production capacity of 35.9 MTPA (million tonnes per annum) and aims to achieve a production capacity of 48.5 MTPA in FY24. Over the next decade, it expects to expand capacity to about 110-130 MTPA.

news.title: Bombay HC asks ED not to take possession of assets of ARA properties
news.para: The adjudicating authority (AA) under the Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA) had recently confirmed the provisional attachments of assets of ARA properties.

news.title: RBI's nod for financing to help bolster self-redevelopment projects in Mumbai
news.para: Real estate projects involving redevelopment and rehabilitation are the mainstay of Mumbai’s property market as the land-starved city has very few vacant land parcels.

news.title: Varanasi: 24 residential buildings, hotels asked to get NOC from fire department
news.para: The CP said that apart from residential all high rise commercial buildings including hotels had been covered under this audit process by the fire brigade officials.

news.title: Property registrations in Hyderabad rose by 152% in May: Report
news.para: The total value of properties transacted in May 2022 stood at Rs 3,058 crore, a 146 per cent YoY and 9.9 per cent MoM rise, taking the cumulative value of all properties registered since January 2022 to Rs 15,071 crore, it said.

news.title: HC tells Housing Board Haryana to refund money to applicants
news.para: Those who had applied for other schemes including those in Faridabad, Mahendergarh, Dadri and Rohtak shall have to be refunded by the board by October 31.

news.title: Pune: Hint of separate meters for EV chargers in new housing societies
news.para: Officials of the Maharashtra State Electricity Distribution Corporation Limited present at a meeting of the EV cell suggested that new residential housing societies should have a separate meter for EV chargers to avail the benefits of subsidised tariffs.

news.title: Government approves six town planning schemes for Ahmedabad & Vadodara
news.para: The lone final TP scheme sanctioned on Wednesday is also from the AMC, TP scheme No. 37 (Danilimda North), a release from the CMO said.

news.title: Blasting takes toll on residents of Hyderabad
news.para: Residents of areas such as Kukatpally, Jubilee Hills, Madhavpuri Hills, Hitech City, Nallagandla, and Raidurg, among others, complain that noise from the rock blasting, movement of heavy machinery as well as construction work during night hours.

news.title: YEIDA set to float infra bonds for its upcoming projects
news.para: The last date of submission of the bid is June 20, while it will be opened on June 21 to select the merchant banker, according to officials.
